Harmony CEO ‘Reasonably Confident’ of Reaching Wage Accord to End Strike

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-08-02T07:14:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/harmony-ceo-reasonably-confident-of-reaching-wage-accord-to-end-strike.html
Harmony Gold Mining Co. Chief
Executive Officer Graham Briggs said he is “reasonably
confident” that a wage agreement will be reached with striking
workers that halted output at its South African mines.  Briggs made the comments in an interview in Johannesburg
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
